    title: CDC WONDER
    description: CDC WONDER is an online query system provided by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention that gives public access to a wide range of health statistics and epidemiologic data collected by CDC programs.
    title_snapshot: 'CDC WONDER - Drug overdose deaths in the US'
    description_snapshot: |-
      The National Center for Health Statistics (NCHS) at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention collects information on deaths involving drugs commonly associated with fatal overdose. This information is available in a searchable database called CDC Wonder.
